[Hyeyeon: Same, something with ice floating in it.]

691
00:33:22,540 --> 00:33:24,610
[Hyeyeon: Oh, it's beautiful.]

692
00:33:25,950 --> 00:33:29,690
[The ocean is fully visible
through the floor-to-ceiling windows]

693
00:33:30,220 --> 00:33:32,180
[Eunchae: The view is stunning.]
[Hyeyeon: Right.]

694
00:33:32,180 --> 00:33:34,340
[Hyeyeon: The water is so blue.]

695
00:33:34,340 --> 00:33:36,890
[Eunchae: It's been a while
since I saw an ocean this clear.]

696
00:33:36,890 --> 00:33:37,960
[Hyeyeon: Yes.]

697
00:33:41,430 --> 00:33:42,620
[Wow.]

698
00:33:42,620 --> 00:33:46,500
[Hyeyeon: The ocean is gorgeous!
Want to play in the water today?]

699
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:49,970
[Eunchae: You go in first, I'll follow you.]

700
00:33:49,970 --> 00:33:51,840
[Eunchae: I mean it.]

701
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:54,780
[Hyeyeon: Didn't you go on a date
with Jinwoo yesterday?]

702
00:33:54,780 --> 00:33:57,450
[Hyeyeon: Did you have fun?]

703
00:33:57,450 --> 00:34:00,120
[Eunchae': True feelings about yesterday's date?]
[Hyeyeon: Yeah.]

704
00:34:00,120 --> 00:34:01,720
[Hyeyeon: Review it!]
[Eunchae: A review...]

705
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:04,120
[Hyeyeon: I'm not Jinwoo, after all.]
[Eunchae: A review...]

706
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:06,260
[Eunchae: Let me give it a score first,
since it's a review.]

707
00:34:06,260 --> 00:34:07,860
[Hyeyeon: Okay, out of five.]
[Eunchae: Out of five.]

708
00:34:07,860 --> 00:34:09,460
[Hyeyeon: Half points allowed?]
[Eunchae: Half points allowed.]

709
00:34:09,730 --> 00:34:12,780
[Pondering]

710
00:34:12,780 --> 00:34:14,420
[Hyeyeon: 2.5?]
[Eunchae: 3.]

711
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:16,400
[Hyeyeon: 3.]
[Eunchae: Somewhere around there.]

712
00:34:16,400 --> 00:34:19,070
[Hyeyeon: So what was missing
from those two points?]

713
00:34:19,070 --> 00:34:21,199
[Hyeyeon: Because there were no sparks?]

714
00:34:21,199 --> 00:34:24,409
[Eunchae: Exactly as you guessed.]

715
00:34:24,409 --> 00:34:27,610
[Eunchae: It felt more like a friendship.]
[Hyeyeon: Sparks... Ah, a friend vibe.]

716
00:34:28,139 --> 00:34:30,380
[Eunchae: We had great conversations, too.]
[Hyeyeon: Just average.]

717
00:34:30,380 --> 00:34:31,500
[Eunchae: Yeah.]

718
00:34:32,420 --> 00:34:34,280
[Eunchae: Since there were no sparks,]

719
00:34:34,550 --> 00:34:37,489
[Hyeyeon: A 3.]
[Eunchae: I can't give it a high score.]

720
00:34:37,489 --> 00:34:41,219
[Hyeyeon: So, which do you prefer? A relationship
that feels more like best friends,

721
00:34:41,219 --> 00:34:44,159
[Hyeyeon: or one where you're obviously a couple]

722
00:34:44,159 --> 00:34:45,760
[Hyeyeon: and still get butterflies
around each other?]

723
00:34:45,760 --> 00:34:49,380
[Eunchae: I think having some level of sparks is better.]
[Hyeyeon: Sparks? Same here.]

724
00:34:49,380 --> 00:34:53,100
[Hyeyeon: I don't really like
friend-like relationships.]

725
00:34:53,100 --> 00:34:56,170
[Hyeyeon: I already have plenty of friends.]

726
00:34:58,460 --> 00:35:00,460
[Hyeyeon: If a relationship
is just like being friends,]

727
00:35:00,460 --> 00:35:04,820
[Hyeyeon: I might as well
just hang out with my actual friends.]
[Eunchae: Right, I agree.]

728
00:35:04,820 --> 00:35:08,720
[Eunchae: There has to be
that romantic spark between a couple.]
[Hyeyeon: Looks like lovers.]

729
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:10,590
[Hyeyeon: It has to make my heart race.]
[Eunchae: Exactly.]

730
00:35:10,590 --> 00:35:13,520
[Eunchae: That's the kind I prefer.]

731
00:35:14,320 --> 00:35:15,860
[Hyeyeon: Let's dig in.]
[Eunchae: Shall we try it?]

732
00:35:15,860 --> 00:35:17,740
[Hyeyeon: Didn't you]

733
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:19,400
[Hyeyeon: barely eat back at the dorm?]

734
00:35:19,400 --> 00:35:21,530
[Eunchae: Yeah, that's true.]

735
00:35:21,530 --> 00:35:23,400
[Hyeyeon: I've been keeping an eye on you.]

736
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:25,000
[Eunchae: Really? Did I miss meals?]

737
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:28,200
[Hyeyeon: Yep, I've been watching you.]

738
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,340
[Hyeyeon: When cleaning up the table,
I checked your bowl]

739
00:35:30,340 --> 00:35:32,210
[Hyeyeon: to see how much food you left.]

740
00:35:32,210 --> 00:35:37,280
[Hyeyeon: I got worried seeing you eat
so little for breakfast.]

741
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,420
[Eunchae: But normally, for breakfast, I...]

742
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:41,020
[Hyeyeon: Skip it?]
[Eunchae: Yeah, I usually skip breakfast.]

743
00:35:41,020 --> 00:35:42,890
[Hyeyeon: Honestly, I do too.]

744
00:35:42,890 --> 00:35:44,750
[Eunchae: What?]

745
00:35:44,750 --> 00:35:47,960
[Hyeyeon: I'd skip it too,
but you ate way too little.]

746
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:51,780
[Eunchae: Yeah, I really couldn't eat much
because I was a bit nervous.]

747
00:35:51,780 --> 00:35:55,700
[Eunchae: The person I talked to the most was Sujin.]

748
00:35:55,860 --> 00:35:57,830
[Eunchae: As for Hyeyeon, I wasn't sure.]

749
00:35:57,830 --> 00:36:00,500
[Eunchae: If I'd gotten to know her sooner,]

750
00:36:00,500 --> 00:36:02,640
[Eunchae:  I think I would've]

751
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:06,640
[Eunchae: hit YES for Hyeyeon.]

752
00:36:07,180 --> 00:36:10,650
[Hyeyeon: I'm just purely curious about this.]
[Eunchae: Yeah.]

753
00:36:10,650 --> 00:36:12,520
[Hyeyeon: Among the girls,]

754
00:36:12,520 --> 00:36:15,180
[Hyeyeon: did you ever secretly think
that if you spent more time together,]

755
00:36:15,180 --> 00:36:17,850
[Hyeyeon: you might develop feelings for her?]

756
00:36:17,850 --> 00:36:20,140
[Eunchae: Of course, for everyone.]
[Hyeyeon: Really?]

757
00:36:20,140 --> 00:36:23,220
[Eunchae: I honestly...]

758
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:27,200
[Eunchae: wanted to meet everyone
at least once first.]

759
00:36:27,660 --> 00:36:29,070
[Eunchae: But it wasn't possible...]

760
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:32,270
[Eunchae: Even though I can't go on
a 1-on-1 date every day,]

761
00:36:32,270 --> 00:36:36,540
[Eunchae: I still want to date as much
as possible to get to know each other.]
[Hyeyeon: That's good.]

762
00:36:36,540 --> 00:36:40,810
[Eunchae: We don't know what everyone is like.]
[Hyeyeon: Right, barely any chances to talk.]

763
00:36:40,810 --> 00:36:44,280
[Eunchae: That's why I came here.]
[Hyeyeon: That's why.]

764
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,680
[Hyeyeon: Okay, I'm really curious about]

765
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:48,550
[Hyeyeon: what choices you'll make later.]

766
00:36:48,550 --> 00:36:51,490
[Eunchae: Of course, I have to try harder,
much harder.]

767
00:36:51,490 --> 00:36:54,340
[Hyeyeon: Now, half... half
of the time has passed.]

768
00:36:54,340 --> 00:36:56,420
[Hyeyeon: With the remaining half,
I wonder how much things will change.]

769
00:36:56,420 --> 00:36:58,430
[Eunchae: Exactly.]
[Hyeyeon: I'm excited.]

770
00:36:58,430 --> 00:37:03,500
[Eunchae: Usually, there would
be a lot of changes at the end.]
[Hyeyeon: Yeah, a total flip.]

771
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:03,500
Totally.

772
00:37:03,500 --> 00:37:06,440
[Hyeyeon: For example, if we go back
from today's date and they don't pick me,]

773
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:09,640
[Hyeyeon: the next day, out of spite,]

774
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:11,510
[Hyeyeon: I send it to someone else.]

775
00:37:11,510 --> 00:37:14,180
[Hyeyeon: But the person I actually like
sends it to me.]

776
00:37:14,180 --> 00:37:17,110
[Hyeyeon: Then the two completely miss each other.]

777
00:37:17,110 --> 00:37:18,450
[Hyeyeon: What would you do
if that happened to you?]

778
00:37:18,450 --> 00:37:21,650
[Eunchae: If I really liked them, of course]

779
00:37:21,650 --> 00:37:23,250
[Eunchae: I'd explain it clearly
because I wouldn't want to miss out.]

780
00:37:21,860 --> 00:37:22,610
-Explain? -I'd explain it clearly

781
00:37:22,610 --> 00:37:23,790
because I wouldn't want to miss out.

782
00:37:23,790 --> 00:37:27,260
[Eunchae: If you don't clear the air
and just let it go,]

783
00:37:27,260 --> 00:37:29,660
[Eunchae: even if you reconnect later,]

784
00:37:29,660 --> 00:37:32,060
[Eunchae: it'll come back to bite you later.]

785
00:37:32,060 --> 00:37:35,530
[Eunchae: It'll come back to bite you later.

786
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:34,970
-It will definitely come back. -Come back.

787
00:37:35,530 --> 00:37:39,800
[Eunchae: I'm the type who absolutely
has to sort things out when an issue comes up.]

788
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:42,470
[Hyeyeon: So if you fight with your partner,]

789
00:37:42,470 --> 00:37:45,680
[Hyeyeon: you're the type
who must make up immediately?]

790
00:37:45,680 --> 00:37:47,540
[Eunchae: I'd give us both some time,]

791
00:37:47,540 --> 00:37:50,060
[Eunchae: but it would be very brief.]

792
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:52,350
[Hyeyeon: How long?]
[Eunchae: I...]

793
00:37:52,350 --> 00:37:53,420
[Eunchae: For example,]

794
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:56,090
[Eunchae: if you and I got
into a fight right here...]

795
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:56,120
-Got into a fight... -If we fought...

796
00:37:56,090 --> 00:37:57,950
[Hyeyeon: I tell you not to order this,
but you still do.]

797
00:37:57,950 --> 00:38:01,690
[Hyeyeon: I want the one with raspberries,
but you won't buy it for me.]

798
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:03,290
[Eunchae: Then,]

799
00:38:03,290 --> 00:38:06,500
[Eunchae: I'd try to talk to them]

800
00:38:06,500 --> 00:38:07,830
[Eunchae: that same afternoon or evening.]

801
00:38:08,660 --> 00:38:11,570
[Eunchae: About that long. It's very short.]

802
00:38:11,570 --> 00:38:14,770
[Eunchae: The next day at the latest.]

803
00:38:14,770 --> 00:38:15,700
[Hyeyeon: Then what if]

804
00:38:15,700 --> 00:38:18,240
[Hyeyeon: you don't really want
to talk right then,]

805
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:21,180
[Hyeyeon: but the other person keeps talking?]

806
00:38:21,180 --> 00:38:26,250
[Eunchae: Then I'd just say whatever comes to mind.]

807
00:38:26,250 --> 00:38:30,250
[Eunchae: I can also predict
that if that happens,]

808
00:38:26,380 --> 00:38:29,790
-The conversation... -I can also predict

809
00:38:29,790 --> 00:38:33,210
that if that happens,

810
00:38:30,250 --> 00:38:34,790
[Right.]
[Eunchae: the other person's reaction won't be good.]

811
00:38:34,790 --> 00:38:36,930
[Eunchae: And then I'll add,]

812
00:38:36,930 --> 00:38:41,460
[Eunchae: "See? You haven't sorted out your thoughts yet,]

813
00:38:41,460 --> 00:38:43,600
[Eunchae: which caused this situation.]

814
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:47,600
[Eunchae: Let's talk again
when we're both rational."]

815
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:53,210
[Eunchae: That way, the misunderstandings
can be cleared up too.]

816
00:38:53,210 --> 00:38:59,080
[Eunchae: I prefer letting them realize why]

817
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:02,290
[Eunchae: I wanted to wait
until things are sorted out.]

818
00:39:02,290 --> 00:39:04,950
[Hyeyeon: If you say something without thinking,]

819
00:39:04,950 --> 00:39:08,690
[Hyeyeon: your partner might grab onto it]

820
00:39:08,690 --> 00:39:12,820
[Hyeyeon: and be like, "See?
That's how you really feel."]

821
00:39:13,020 --> 00:39:14,380
[Disgust]

822
00:39:14,380 --> 00:39:16,970
[Hyeyeon: Already tired?
It feels like we're actually dating?]

823
00:39:16,970 --> 00:39:18,830
[Hyeyeon: The way they talk can really
get your blood pressure up. For example…]

824
00:39:18,830 --> 00:39:20,700
[Hyeyeon: "Isn't that just what you thought?"]
[Eunchae: Just admit it.]

825
00:39:20,700 --> 00:39:23,370
[Hyeyeon: "It's not about admitting it.
That's exactly what you're thinking right now."]

826
00:39:23,370 --> 00:39:24,970
[Hyeyeon: "You thought it,
and you even said it to me."]

827
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:29,250
[Eunchae: I'm sorry.]
[Hyeyeon: "So that's really how you see me."]

828
00:39:29,570 --> 00:39:30,050
I'm sorry.

829
00:39:30,050 --> 00:39:32,720
[Hyeyeon: Sorry for what?]

830
00:39:32,720 --> 00:39:34,580
[Eunchae: It seems like you do this a lot.]

831
00:39:34,580 --> 00:39:36,990
[Eunchae: You've probably driven plenty
of people up the wall.]

832
00:39:36,990 --> 00:39:39,920
[Hyeyeon: I've heard that so many times
I could recite it.]

833
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:45,530
[Hyeyeon: I've been through it so often that I already
know what they're going to say next.]

834
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:49,270
[Getting to know sides of each other they'd never seen before]

835
00:39:49,800 --> 00:39:54,070
[Their time together flows at the same pace]

836
00:39:58,070 --> 00:39:59,940
[Sujin: We also...]

837
00:39:59,940 --> 00:40:03,410
[Sujin: Didn't they have those couple bracelets?]

838
00:40:03,410 --> 00:40:07,150
[Heejin: What bracelets?]
[Sujin: Hyeyeon and Seungho.]

839
00:40:07,150 --> 00:40:10,090
[Sujin: We're wearing couple rings, too.]

840
00:40:10,090 --> 00:40:12,100
[Heejin: But ours looks way better.]

841
00:40:12,100 --> 00:40:13,560
[Of course.]
[Heejin: But ours looks way better.]

842
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:15,420
[Sujin: They can't even compare to ours.]

843
00:40:15,420 --> 00:40:16,490
[Sujin: Ours is better.]

844
00:40:16,490 --> 00:40:18,890
[Heejin: Theirs will just gather dust in a drawer.]

845
00:40:18,890 --> 00:40:21,300
[Sujin: Ours definitely won't end up in a drawer?]

846
00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:22,370
[Sujin: We'll keep wearing them.]

847
00:40:22,370 --> 00:40:23,430
[Heejin: Yes.]

848
00:40:23,430 --> 00:40:25,030
[Heejin: Plus, I really love rings.]

849
00:40:25,030 --> 00:40:26,640
[Sujin: That's true.]

850
00:40:26,640 --> 00:40:28,500
[Sujin: I'm going to show it off everywhere.]

851
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:30,110
[Sujin: Notice anything different about me?]

852
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:32,240
[Heejin: You know? Doing that on purpose.]

853
00:40:32,240 --> 00:40:34,110
[Sujin: What was that again?]

854
00:40:33,570 --> 00:40:34,700
After putting it on,

855
00:40:36,250 --> 00:40:38,910
[Heejin: when washing hands,
suddenly take off the ring.]

856
00:40:38,910 --> 00:40:41,850
[Sujin: "Ah, I need to go wash my hands."]

857
00:40:41,850 --> 00:40:43,190
[Sujin: "Oh?" Then put it back on.]

858
00:40:44,790 --> 00:40:47,190
[Sujin: First of all, the vibe Heejin gave me was]

859
00:40:47,190 --> 00:40:51,190
[Sujin: that she likes joking around
more than I thought.]

860
00:40:51,190 --> 00:40:53,600
[Sujin: When I date,]

861
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:58,670
[Sujin: I like playful relationships
where we tease each other.]

862
00:40:58,670 --> 00:41:02,140
[Sujin: I felt like she fits that perfectly.]

863
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:08,010
[Heejin: It'll turn out really pretty.]

864
00:41:08,010 --> 00:41:11,210
[Hold it like this,
like holding a pencil or a pen.]

865
00:41:11,210 --> 00:41:14,150
[Hold the ring with your other hand.]

866
00:41:14,150 --> 00:41:18,690
[Just sand it back and forth like this.]

867
00:41:19,490 --> 00:41:21,090
[Like this.]

868
00:41:21,090 --> 00:41:23,230
[Sujin: It's starting to change color.]

869
00:41:21,260 --> 00:41:23,230
-A little bit. -The color changed a bit.

870
00:41:23,230 --> 00:41:26,160
[Once you're done with this step,
you're finished polishing it.]

871
00:41:32,100 --> 00:41:34,820
[Skilled]

872
00:41:37,640 --> 00:41:41,380
[Sujin is paying close attention to details]

873
00:41:42,180 --> 00:41:43,580
[Heejin: Going smoothly?]

874
00:41:43,580 --> 00:41:45,920
[Sujin: The twisted pattern is so hard to polish.]

875
00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:50,990
[Sujin: I can't really reach the twisted pattern.]
[Heejin: Use a little more pressure.]

876
00:41:53,390 --> 00:41:57,130
[Heejin: She did it very carefully
and meticulously.]

877
00:41:57,130 --> 00:41:59,260
[Heejin: And she did a great job.]

878
00:41:59,260 --> 00:42:02,730
[Heejin: She nailed it right
after listening to the teacher.]

879
00:42:02,730 --> 00:42:07,000
[Heejin: That made me feel like
she's really quick with her hands.]

880
00:42:07,540 --> 00:42:09,940
[Sujin: But my hands turned black.]

881
00:42:09,940 --> 00:42:11,540
[Sujin: How are your hands whiter than mine?]

882
00:42:11,540 --> 00:42:14,480
[Sujin: I polished this so hard. See that?]

883
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:17,410
[Sujin: Look how hard I worked.]

884
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:19,010
[Heejin: I polished hard, too.]

885
00:42:19,010 --> 00:42:21,420
[Sujin: I want to make it
as smooth as possible for you.]

886
00:42:21,420 --> 00:42:24,620
[Smooth, smooth.]

887
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,560
[Sujin: Look how much I polished it.]

888
00:42:27,560 --> 00:42:29,160
[Heejin: Your hands are so pretty.]

889
00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:31,030
[Sujin: Really?]
[Heejin: Let me see.]

890
00:42:31,030 --> 00:42:33,960
[Sujin: But it's a bit rough here.
This part is okay.]
[Heejin: It's pretty.]

891
00:42:34,500 --> 00:42:38,230
[They naturally held hands]

892
00:42:38,230 --> 00:42:39,570
[Heejin: Your hands are so pretty.]

893
00:42:39,570 --> 00:42:42,240
[Sujin: I take after my mom.]
[Heejin: Your mom must have pretty hands too.]

894
00:42:40,490 --> 00:42:42,380
-Mom. -Your mom must have pretty hands too.

895
00:42:42,240 --> 00:42:44,910
[Sujin: My hands are exactly like my mom's.]

896
00:42:44,910 --> 00:42:46,510
[Heejin: They're really pretty.]

897
00:42:46,510 --> 00:42:48,910
[Sujin: Does it hurt a little here?]

898
00:42:48,910 --> 00:42:50,510
[Heejin: It hurt this morning.]

899
00:42:49,100 --> 00:42:50,570
-Are you okay? -It hurt this morning.

900
00:42:50,510 --> 00:42:52,650
[Sujin: Then why didn't you put a band-aid on
before coming out?]

901
00:42:52,650 --> 00:42:53,980
[Heejin: Because I wash my hands a lot.]

902
00:42:53,980 --> 00:42:56,390
[Heejin: Even if I put one on, it falls off.]

903
00:42:56,390 --> 00:42:59,590
[Sujin: Waterproof band-aids.]
[Heejin: I didn't bring any.]

904
00:42:59,590 --> 00:43:00,920
[Sujin: I think I have some.]

905
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:03,860
[Heejin: You have them too? Are you Doraemon?]

906
00:43:04,130 --> 00:43:06,260
[Sujin: If you look closely, I have everything.]

907
00:43:06,260 --> 00:43:08,130
[Sujin: Or maybe I don't.]

908
00:43:08,130 --> 00:43:11,070
[Sujin: I'll put one on for you when we get back.]

909
00:43:11,070 --> 00:43:13,200
[Heejin: When we get back today...]

910
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:16,940
[Heejin: Like yesterday, can you draw
my aegyo-sal for me?]

911
00:43:16,940 --> 00:43:20,680
[Sujin: Aegyo-sal? Oh... sure. You should've just said so. Why didn't you?]

912
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:21,740
[Heejin: I don't know.]

913
00:43:21,740 --> 00:43:24,680
[Sujin: Then I'll do it for you when we get back.]

914
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:26,410
[Sujin: I'll do it for you tomorrow. Tomorrow
I'll draw your aegyo-sal.]

915
00:43:26,410 --> 00:43:28,150
[Heejin: Okay.]

916
00:43:28,150 --> 00:43:31,620
[Sujin: Looks like you were really happy with
the aegyo-sal I drew last time.]

917
00:43:31,620 --> 00:43:32,690
[Sujin: I'm proud of that.]

918
00:43:35,890 --> 00:43:39,900
[Now for the final polish. Spin the machine
to finish it off]

919
00:43:39,900 --> 00:43:42,030
[Sujin: Okay.]
[Heejin: Okay.]

920
00:43:43,460 --> 00:43:47,900
[Paying even more attention
to the finishing touches]

921
00:43:50,540 --> 00:43:53,020
[Carefully]

922
00:43:54,310 --> 00:43:57,220
[Heejin: It's so much brighter
than before, right?]

923
00:43:57,220 --> 00:43:57,760
[Sparkling]

924
00:43:57,760 --> 00:43:58,310
[Heejin: It's so much brighter
than before, right?]

925
00:43:58,310 --> 00:43:59,650
[Sujin: It's going to look great.]

926
00:43:59,650 --> 00:44:00,980
[Heejin: Right?]

927
00:44:00,980 --> 00:44:06,060
[Sujin: It's so shiny that even if we don't
show it off, everyone will notice.]

928
00:44:06,860 --> 00:44:09,790
[Though their hands got dirty,
the rings begin to shine]

929
00:44:10,860 --> 00:44:14,600
[The ring made for Heejin]

930
00:44:14,860 --> 00:44:19,400
[The ring made for Sujin]

931
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:25,010
[What kind of meaning will the rings they made
for each other hold for the two of them?]

932
00:44:27,410 --> 00:44:30,740
[The rings are done. Try them on]

933
00:44:31,500 --> 00:44:33,140
[Wow]

934
00:44:33,140 --> 00:44:34,620
[Wow, thank you]

935
00:44:34,620 --> 00:44:37,290
[Checking if the size fits.]

936
00:44:38,090 --> 00:44:40,220
[Heejin: You did such a great job.]

937
00:44:40,220 --> 00:44:42,090
[Sujin: Pass? Is it good enough to pass?]

938
00:44:42,090 --> 00:44:43,690
[Heejin: Yes, I'm really satisfied.]
[Sujin: This part is really shiny, right?]

939
00:44:43,690 --> 00:44:46,100
[Heejin: Really.]
[Sujin: You saw my hand earlier, didn't you?]

940
00:44:46,100 --> 00:44:47,430
[Heejin: Yes. Thank you so much.]

941
00:44:47,430 --> 00:44:49,420
[Heejin: Wow, you did such a great job.]

942
00:44:49,420 --> 00:44:53,980
[A couple ring that was worth all the effort]

943
00:44:49,550 --> 00:44:51,090
-Does it fit? -Yes.

944
00:44:54,300 --> 00:44:55,020
[Heejin: Thank you.]

945
00:44:55,020 --> 00:44:55,970
[Good work.]

946
00:44:55,970 --> 00:44:58,640
[Sujin: Thank you.]

947
00:44:58,640 --> 00:45:01,840
[Sujin: Hold this. no, I want to take
a photo like this.]

948
00:45:01,840 --> 00:45:03,450
[Sujin: With the best angle.]

949
00:45:03,450 --> 00:45:04,780
[Heejin: Should we take a photo?]

950
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:06,650
[Heejin: Like this.]

951
00:45:08,020 --> 00:45:13,320
[Heejin and Sujin, wearing the rings and creating
memories just for the two of them]

952
00:45:18,540 --> 00:45:19,460
[Sujin: The best.]

953
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:21,330
[Heejin: The best angle.]

954
00:45:21,330 --> 00:45:22,670
[Sujin: That's not the best angle~]

955
00:45:22,670 --> 00:45:25,870
[Heejin: Okay, don't get mad.]

956
00:45:25,870 --> 00:45:29,070
[Sujin: Rather than it being
at the best angle, it's too.]

957
00:45:29,070 --> 00:45:30,940
[Sujin: I made the ring.]

958
00:45:30,940 --> 00:45:33,080
[Sujin: And we took a photo together.]

959
00:45:33,080 --> 00:45:35,210
[Sujin: That's what I remember the most.]

960
00:45:35,210 --> 00:45:40,020
[Sujin: We took a selfie together showing off
our couple rings.]

961
00:45:40,020 --> 00:45:44,020
[Sujin: It looked like we were a real couple,
so it felt good.]

962
00:45:44,820 --> 00:45:48,020
[Heejin: I'm not just saying this to be nice—
I really love it.]

963
00:45:48,020 --> 00:45:48,560
[Sujin: Me too.]

964
00:45:48,560 --> 00:45:50,160
[Heejin: Thank you.]

965
00:45:50,160 --> 00:45:51,760
[Sujin: Thank you too.]

966
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:53,360
[Heejin: I'm going to wear it for a long time.]

967
00:45:53,360 --> 00:45:54,430
[Sujin: I'm never taking it off.]

968
00:45:55,500 --> 00:45:57,100
[Sujin: I'll wear it forever.]

969
00:45:58,430 --> 00:46:01,820
[Heejin: I'll do surprise checks.]
[Sujin: Okay. Anytime.]

970
00:46:01,820 --> 00:46:04,310
[Heejin: You seem pretty confident.]
[Sujin: Of course. Anytime.]

971
00:46:04,310 --> 00:46:06,980
[Sujin: Starting today. From this moment on.]

972
00:46:06,980 --> 00:46:10,260
[Heejin: Okay.]
[Sujin: The surprise check begins.]

973
00:46:11,250 --> 00:46:13,380
[Heejin: She said that with such confidence.
Was she really sure she could follow through?]

974
00:46:13,380 --> 00:46:15,520
[Heejin: The way I saw it, if you can't keep
a promise, you shouldn't make it so easily.]

975
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:17,650
[Heejin: But even if it was just to please
the other person.]

976
00:46:17,650 --> 00:46:20,590
[Heejin: if you can't do it, you wouldn't make
that kind of promise lightly.]

977
00:46:20,590 --> 00:46:23,530
[Heejin: So I thought she must be
serious about it.]

978
00:46:23,530 --> 00:46:28,330
[Heejin: It must have been sincere.]

979
00:46:28,860 --> 00:46:31,270
[Sujin: Of course I felt that way.]

980
00:46:31,270 --> 00:46:34,740
[Sujin: Since we made couple rings together with
someone I've been wanting to go on a date with.]

981
00:46:34,740 --> 00:46:36,500
[Sujin: it meant a lot.]

982
00:46:36,500 --> 00:46:40,880
[Sujin: And I wanted to show everyone that
we're wearing couple rings.]

983
00:46:40,880 --> 00:46:43,010
[Sujin: I hoped Heejin would
feel the same way too.]

984
00:46:43,010 --> 00:46:47,280
[Sujin: I hoped she wouldn't take the ring off.
That's what I was thinking.]

985
00:46:47,820 --> 00:46:49,150
[Sujin: Let's go.]

986
00:46:49,150 --> 00:46:52,090
[Heejin: Let's go?]
[Sujin: Yeah.]

987
00:46:52,090 --> 00:46:54,490
[Sujin: Because I need to hurry up
and show everyone.]

988
00:46:54,490 --> 00:46:56,890
[Heejin: Let's go.]
[Sujin: And we took a lot of photos too.]

989
00:46:58,230 --> 00:47:02,230
[Heejin: I didn't feel any particularly
strong flutter.]

990
00:47:02,500 --> 00:47:06,240
[Heejin: Sujin probably sensed it too?
Because I...]

991
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:08,900
[Heejin: didn't have particularly
strong feelings for her.]

992
00:47:08,900 --> 00:47:12,640
[Heejin: I think she must have felt that too.]

993
00:47:13,710 --> 00:47:17,450
[Sujin: Honestly, even if I got a little hurt]

994
00:47:17,450 --> 00:47:19,580
[Sujin: my first choice, aside from Heejin.]

995
00:47:19,580 --> 00:47:22,520
[Sujin: I never considered anyone else.]

996
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:25,190
[Sujin: So even now, it's still Heejin.]

997
00:47:25,190 --> 00:47:27,860
[Sujin: But the feelings and expectations
I had for Heejin.]

998
00:47:27,860 --> 00:47:31,590
[Sujin: have definitely faded quite a bit.]

999
00:47:31,700 --> 00:47:37,730
[The two wearing couple rings—how will their
relationship unfold from here?]

1000
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:42,270
[Hyeyeon: Anyway, you might break up
eventually, right?]

1001
00:47:42,270 --> 00:47:44,140
[Hyeyeon: Why is that?]

1002
00:47:44,140 --> 00:47:48,410
[Eunchae: I think every time
I'm in a relationship.]

1003
00:47:48,410 --> 00:47:51,880
[Eunchae: love has a limited total amount.]

1004
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:55,080
[Eunchae: There will come a day when that
love is all used up.]

1005
00:47:55,080 --> 00:47:57,490
[Hyeyeon: Someday...]
[Eunchae: I think that day will definitely come.]

1006
00:47:57,490 --> 00:48:00,420
[Eunchae: When that moment arrives...]

1007
00:48:00,420 --> 00:48:02,560
[Eunchae: I'll naturally let go.]

1008
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:07,100
[Eunchae: If I no longer have the will.]

1009
00:48:07,100 --> 00:48:09,500
[Eunchae: to keep the relationship going.]

1010
00:48:09,460 --> 00:48:11,250
-Then that relationship for me... -Right.

1011
00:48:09,500 --> 00:48:12,970
[Eunchae: then that relationship no longer
holds meaning for me.]

1012
00:48:14,040 --> 00:48:16,440
[Eunchae: And holding on too tightly.]

1013
00:48:16,440 --> 00:48:19,640
[Eunchae: hurts the other person too.]

1014
00:48:16,690 --> 00:48:18,300
-Hurts the other person too.

1015
00:48:18,300 --> 00:48:19,910
-It's not a good thing either.

1016
00:48:19,640 --> 00:48:22,850
[Eunchae: And the other person doesn't
want that either.]

1017
00:48:22,850 --> 00:48:27,650
[Hyeyeon: That's so sad.]
[Eunchae: So I've always thought]

1018
00:48:27,650 --> 00:48:31,920
[Eunchae: that when you can love,
you should love well.]

1019
00:48:31,920 --> 00:48:33,260
[Hyeyeon: That's nice.]

1020
00:48:32,700 --> 00:48:33,360
[Right?]

1021
00:48:33,260 --> 00:48:35,120
[Eunchae: Because nothing lasts forever.]

1022
00:48:35,120 --> 00:48:38,330
[Hyeyeon: I think real love involves fighting.]

1023
00:48:38,330 --> 00:48:41,530
[Hyeyeon: You speak up about your grievances
and have a fight.]

1024
00:48:41,530 --> 00:48:43,930
[Hyeyeon: Being honest about all those grievances]

1025
00:48:43,930 --> 00:48:45,800
[Hyeyeon: I really like that kind of dynamic.]

1026
00:48:45,800 --> 00:48:49,810
[Hyeyeon: Fighting appropriately keeps
a relationship healthy. But...]

1027
00:48:49,810 --> 00:48:54,080
[Hyeyeon: If there's a problem with this person,
or if something comes up between us.]

1028
00:48:54,080 --> 00:48:57,010
[Hyeyeon: we still need to talk about things
that might turn into arguments.]

1029
00:48:57,010 --> 00:49:00,480
[Hyeyeon: But sometimes that energy just
disappears all of a sudden.]

1030
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:01,550
[Hyeyeon: Like if I say]

1031
00:49:01,550 --> 00:49:04,490
[Hyeyeon: "You shouldn't have done that
back then"]

1032
00:49:04,490 --> 00:49:06,090
[Hyeyeon: and the other person just goes,
"Oh, okay then".]

1033
00:49:06,090 --> 00:49:09,830
[Hyeyeon: I'd feel completely deflated.]

1034
00:49:09,830 --> 00:49:11,430
[Hyeyeon: The other person doesn't even
want to fight with me.]

1035
00:49:11,430 --> 00:49:13,030
[Eunchae: If they avoid it]

1036
00:49:13,030 --> 00:49:15,160
[Hyeyeon: Not even wanting to fight means]

1037
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:19,170
[Hyeyeon: they don't want to improve
the relationship with me anymore.]

1038
00:49:19,700 --> 00:49:22,640
[Hyeyeon: Looking at it another way,
maybe it's like what Eunchae said]

1039
00:49:22,640 --> 00:49:25,570
[Hyeyeon: the total amount of love
slowly gets used up]

1040
00:49:25,570 --> 00:49:28,240
[Hyeyeon: and that's why it ends up like this.]

1041
00:49:28,240 --> 00:49:30,650
[Eunchae: It feels like everything connects
in a cycle.]

1042
00:49:30,650 --> 00:49:34,650
[Hyeyeon: Right. Everyone has moments
when they lose heart]

1043
00:49:34,650 --> 00:49:37,050
[Hyeyeon: and times when they get tired.]

1044
00:49:37,050 --> 00:49:39,720
[Hyeyeon: Times when they look tired.]
[Eunchae: Right.]

1045
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:42,930
[Hyeyeon: Who doesn't get tired?]

1046
00:49:43,190 --> 00:49:45,060
[Eunchae: This kind of conversation
feels really nice.]

1047
00:49:45,060 --> 00:49:46,930
[Hyeyeon: Yeah. It's my first time talking about
this kind of stuff since I got here.]

1048
00:49:46,930 --> 00:49:49,330
[Hyeyeon: This is my first time having
this kind of conversation.]

1049
00:49:49,600 --> 00:49:54,670
[Eunchae: The things we talked about at the café.
I've never talked about them]

1050
00:49:54,670 --> 00:49:58,140
[Eunchae: with any of the other guests.]

1051
00:49:58,140 --> 00:50:00,810
[Eunchae: And I usually really enjoy]

1052
00:50:00,810 --> 00:50:03,210
[Eunchae: occasionally having
deeper conversations.]

1053
00:50:03,210 --> 00:50:06,020
[Eunchae: Rather than just being friends,]

1054
00:50:06,020 --> 00:50:11,490
[Eunchae: I felt like there was a subtle,
different vibe between us.]

1055
00:50:12,100 --> 00:50:15,760
[Hyeyeon: She's a bit shy, but our one-on-one
conversation flowed well, and she laughs a lot.]

1056
00:50:15,760 --> 00:50:17,890
[Hyeyeon: But she's not the loud
or boisterous type.]

1057
00:50:17,890 --> 00:50:20,830
[Hyeyeon: She's fun to talk to, yet calm, and]

1058
00:50:20,830 --> 00:50:23,770
[Hyeyeon: through our conversation, we got to
know each other's personalities.]

1059
00:50:23,770 --> 00:50:25,370
[Hyeyeon: So rather than feeling like friends,]

1060
00:50:25,370 --> 00:50:28,040
[Hyeyeon: it felt more like the vibe of lovers.]

1061
00:50:28,300 --> 00:50:32,840
[An unexpected side of her that makes
the heart flutter]

1062
00:50:33,640 --> 00:50:34,970
[Hyeyeon: Be careful. Hold onto me.
It's lower up ahead.]

1063
00:50:34,970 --> 00:50:36,310
[Eunchae: You really have to be careful.
Are you okay?]

1064
00:50:36,310 --> 00:50:37,910
[Hyeyeon: Yeah, I'm fine. Just hold onto me.]

1065
00:50:39,130 --> 00:50:41,400
-It's really high. -It really is.

1066
00:50:39,300 --> 00:50:42,780
[The two naturally hold hands
and walk toward the beach.]

1067
00:50:41,400 --> 00:50:43,120
-But still... -It's really steep.

1068
00:50:42,780 --> 00:50:45,390
[Eunchae: But won't your sandals be slippery?]
[Hyeyeon: Mine?]

1069
00:50:45,390 --> 00:50:46,990
[Hyeyeon: These are flats. Completely flat.]

1070
00:50:46,990 --> 00:50:48,060
[Eunchae: Are you sure you're okay?]
[Hyeyeon: Yeah.]

1071
00:50:48,060 --> 00:50:49,930
[Eunchae: But I'm not okay.]
[Hyeyeon: Right?]

1072
00:50:49,930 --> 00:50:52,330
[Hyeyeon: How about this? Just a little...]
[Eunchae: No, it's fine.]

1073
00:50:52,330 --> 00:50:53,930
[Hyeyeon: Lean your weight toward me a little.]

1074
00:50:57,400 --> 00:50:59,270
[Eunchae: It's okay. Let's just hurry down.]

1075
00:50:59,270 --> 00:51:01,140
[Hyeyeon: Run down?]
[Eunchae: That might actually be better.]

1076
00:51:01,140 --> 00:51:03,270
[Hyeyeon: One, two, three.]

1077
00:51:07,010 --> 00:51:08,610
[Eunchae: This is better.]
[Hyeyeon: Yeah, you're right.]

1078
00:51:08,610 --> 00:51:10,480
[Eunchae: I almost slipped for real.]
[Hyeyeon: We almost died.]

1079
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:12,080
[Eunchae: More sand's going to get
in my shoes now.]

1080
00:51:12,080 --> 00:51:13,680
[Hyeyeon: Can't help it. I got a lot of sand
in mine yesterday too.]

1081
00:51:17,950 --> 00:51:20,890
[Hyeyeon: Wow, the ocean is so beautiful.]

1082
00:51:20,890 --> 00:51:22,490
[Hyeyeon: Oh, it's so pretty.]

1083
00:51:22,490 --> 00:51:24,890
[Eunchae: Really.]

1084
00:51:24,890 --> 00:51:27,030
[Eunchae: It's been a while since I've seen
the ocean this close.]

1085
00:51:27,030 --> 00:51:29,700
[Hyeyeon: Right? Oh, I'm not...]

1086
00:51:29,700 --> 00:51:33,170
[The two take a leisurely stroll along the beach]

1087
00:51:33,440 --> 00:51:34,770
[Hyeyeon: Wow, it's so beautiful.]

1088
00:51:34,770 --> 00:51:37,710
[Hyeyeon: Should we take a picture of the view?]
[Eunchae: Sure.]

1089
00:51:40,640 --> 00:51:45,180
[The moment they capture the ocean together
in their photos]

1090
00:51:40,780 --> 00:51:41,450
Like this.

1091
00:51:47,580 --> 00:51:52,390
[The sound of shutters clicking one after another]

1092
00:51:53,720 --> 00:51:55,320
[Eunchae: I feel a little shy.]

1093
00:51:56,120 --> 00:51:57,730
[Hyeyeon: Come a little closer.]

1094
00:51:57,730 --> 00:51:58,530
[Eunchae: Where?]

1095
00:51:58,530 --> 00:51:59,860
[Hyeyeon: Closer to the waves.]
[Eunchae: Closer to the waves?]

1096
00:51:59,860 --> 00:52:02,000
[Hyeyeon: I'll push you into the water.]

1097
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:05,380
[Eunchae: I won't get swept away
by the waves, will I?]

1098
00:52:05,380 --> 00:52:07,020
[Oh!]

1099
00:52:08,670 --> 00:52:10,270
[Hyeyeon: Seriously, that was close.]

1100
00:52:10,270 --> 00:52:13,210
[Eunchae: Really, I almost fell in the water.]

1101
00:52:13,210 --> 00:52:14,300
[Eunchae: That was so scary.]

1102
00:52:14,300 --> 00:52:16,060
[Hyeyeon: Oh, the waves are getting bigger.]

1103
00:52:16,060 --> 00:52:17,570
[Hyeyeon: Want to go over there
and write something?

1104
00:52:17,570 --> 00:52:19,080
[Eunchae: Sure.]

1105
00:52:23,350 --> 00:52:30,030
[Writing "Eunchae" in the sand with a shell]

1106
00:52:30,030 --> 00:52:31,360
[Eunchae: You write really well?]

1107
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:32,960
[Hyeyeon: Really?]
[Eunchae: Yeah.]

1108
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:34,380
[Hyeyeon: I'll draw a heart
and write "Hyeyeon" too.]

1109
00:52:34,380 --> 00:52:38,380
[Eunchae: Hyeyeon.]

1110
00:52:38,830 --> 00:52:41,620
[Hyeyeon: Uh... uh, what's that? What's
going on? What's going on?!]

1111
00:52:41,740 --> 00:52:43,860
[Oh~ oh no.]

1112
00:52:44,970 --> 00:52:48,440
[Hyeyeon: This is so funny.]

1113
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:50,310
[The names "Eunchae" and "Hyeyeon" get
washed away by the waves]

1114
00:52:49,450 --> 00:52:50,070
[No way]

1115
00:52:50,310 --> 00:52:50,980
[Wow, we need to write faster.]

1116
00:52:50,980 --> 00:52:51,650
[The names "Eunchae" and "Hyeyeon" get washed
away by the waves]

1117
00:52:51,650 --> 00:52:54,580
[Hyeyeon: Right now!]

1118
00:52:54,580 --> 00:52:57,250
[Hyeyeon: This is so hilarious.]

1119
00:52:57,520 --> 00:53:01,790
[Eunchae, Hyeyeon]
[This time she writes it quickly]

1120
00:53:01,790 --> 00:53:05,530
[Eunchae: Walking along the beach with Hyeyeon.]

1121
00:53:05,530 --> 00:53:10,330
[Eunchae: the moment we wrote our names in
the sand is what I'll remember the most.]

1122
00:53:10,330 --> 00:53:13,000
[Eunchae: We were wearing matching outfits.]

1123
00:53:13,000 --> 00:53:15,940
[Eunchae: and I thought the scene
was really beautiful.]

1124
